                        <rdg source="bib:Friederich1855_01">tapa kata</rdg>
                        <rdg source="bib:Holle1867_01 bib:Pleyte1911_03">tapa kava<lb n="2" break="no"/>li</rdg>
                        <rdg source="bib:RichadianaKartakusuma2005_01">tapa<supplied reason="omitted">k</supplied> kavali</rdg>
                    </app>
                    <!--1–2. tapak· valar N HD TSN ◇ tapa kata F; tapa kavali P; tapa‹k› kavali RK. ― 2. nu syi muliA tapa H ◇ nusya muṅi atapa F; nu saṁ hyaṁ muliA tapa P; nu siya muliA tapa N RK; nu siya muliA tapa‹k·› HD TSN. — 2–3. Iña ◇ N HD TSN RK; bhagya F H P. —  6–7. sakulili‹ṁ› H N ◇ sakulili F; sakuliliṁ HD TSN RK; it may be doubted that any panyecek was written here — 8. pa‹n›dǝri ◇ padǝri F; pa‹n›dǝ:ri H N HD TSN RK; pandǝ:ri P. — 9. hǝbǝl ◇ hǝbǝṅ F; hǝ:bǝ:l H P N HD TSN RK.
-->
